comment: A theorem which could be used as sole axiom for the non-logical predicate instead of ~ ax-8 and ~ ax-9 . Indeed, it is implied over propositional calculus by the conjunction of ~ ax-8 and ~ ax-9 , as proved here. In the other direction, one can prove ~ ax-8 (respectively ~ ax-9 ) from ~ bj-ax89 by using ~ mpan2 ( respectively ~ mpan ) and ~ equid . (TODO: move to main part.) (Contributed by BJ, 3-Oct-2019.)
